                <li>If someone purchases a business class ticket and needs to cancel or adjust their reservation, they will be charged between $300 and $400. </li>
                <li>For cancellations of first-class tickets, passengers will be assessed a fee of between $200 and $400. </li>
            </ul>

            <p>In addition, if you rebook a flight at a higher price, the <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/">fare compare</a> to others. You will be responsible for paying the difference in price and the Emirates flight cancellation fee. </p>

            <h3>Conditions to get a Refund on Emirates Airlines </h3>
            <p>According to the airline’s return policy, the company will provide you with a refund in the form of a travel voucher or cash. The airline's refund policy determines whether or not a traveller is entitled to a full or partial refund. The system also allows users to monitor the progress of their repayments. You may request a ticket refund in the following circumstances: </p>


            <ul>
                <li>In case you don’t catch a substitute flight after the Emirates aircraft was cancelled. </li>
                <li>When the Schedule Indicators were modified, you were given the option of taking transportation. </li>
                <li>Additionally, if a refund is required under the terms and conditions of your ticket, you are entitled to one. </li>
                <li>If both your outbound and return flights were scheduled for the same day, and you had to cancel your trip due to a 90-minute flight delay, you are entitled to a reimbursement. </li>
                <li>You can also request a refund if a passenger passes away or your visa application is rejected. </li>
            </ul>

            <p>Additionally, refunds are available if the airline cancels your transcontinental flight because it was more than three hours late. </p>

